UNIVERSITY ACADEMIC POLICIES

1. GRADING SYSTEM
The university uses a letter grade system (A, B, C, D, F) with plus and minus designations.
- A: 70-100 (Excellent)
- B: 60-69 (Good)
- C: 50-59 (Satisfactory)
- D: 40-49 (Poor)
- F: Below 30 (Failing)

2. GRADE APPEALS
Students may appeal grades within 30 days of receiving the grade.
The appeal process involves:
- Informal discussion with instructor
- Formal appeal to department head
- Final appeal to academic affairs committee

3. ACADEMIC MISCONDUCT
Academic misconduct includes:
- Plagiarism
- Cheating on examinations
- Unauthorized collaboration
- Falsification of academic records

Penalties range from warning to expulsion depending on severity.

4. ATTENDANCE POLICY
Regular attendance is expected. Instructors may establish specific attendance requirements.
Excessive absences may result in course failure.

5. GRADUATION REQUIREMENTS
- Minimum 120 credit hours
- Cumulative GPA of 2.0 or higher
- Completion of all major requirements
- Residency requirement: final 30 credits at the university